The paper deals with the problem of recovering signals from under-sampled measurements, which is a common problem in signal processing and information theory (cs.IT, cs.SP). The focus is on analysis-sparse signals, which is a topic of interest in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of statistical dimension, which is a concept from numerical analysis and optimization (cs.NA). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for incorporating prior information, which is a topic of interest in statistical inference and machine learning (cs.SI).
